ent-RMCJumpsuitMarineParaService = paramarine service uniform
    .desc = A formal No.2 service uniform worn by RCM-P officers. Features the same upper torso cut as the No.8 BDU, but paired with pressed khaki trousers. Issued for inspections, ceremonial duties, or when deployed in an advisory role.
    .suffix = Survivor, Paramarine

ent-RMCJumpsuitMarineRoyal = royal marine commando uniform
    .desc = The field uniform of the royal marine commandoes. They have shards of light Kevlar to help protect against stabbing weapons and bullets. Onpar with similar USCMC equipment.
    .suffix = Filled, Royal

